description: Three large frogs are gathered around a formal dining table set with plates, cutlery, and various dishes. The dishes include a bowl filled with flies resembling a salad, a stick of butter on a plate, bread slices on a plate, and a bowl of spherical objects that appear to be eggs. One frog, significantly larger than the others, sits in the center with a distressed expression and holds a fork and knife, contemplating the meal. Another frog on the left reaches towards the bowl of flies with a webbed hand. The scene presents an absurd domestic setting where amphibians consume their natural prey with human-like formality, highlighting the surreal juxtaposition of animal behavior and human customs.
caption: "Sidney, just take one  don't handle every fly."
